Package frc.discordslackbot.commands

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractCommand
    The template for a command from a brobot
    AbstractCommand.AbstractCommandData
    Very important.
    AbstractCommand.AbstractCommandResponse
    Very important.
    AbstractCommand.ContinuePersistingCommandResponse
    This is halfway to being an enum, hence the private constructor and public static final field.
    AbstractCommand.GenericCommandData
    Nothing special, just an instantiatable AbstractCommand.AbstractCommandData
    AbstractCommand.GenericCommandResponse
    Nothing special, just an instantiatable AbstractCommand.AbstractCommandResponse with an optional callback.
    CurrentTelemetryCommand
    Simple command that works with AbstractRobotTelemetry to get the current location and heading of the robot
    DriveDistanceCommand
    This very nice command will make the robot drive! Similar to a point-to-point auton, this command does not steer, it just drives in a straight line and it is up to the user to command turns and remain clear of obstacles
    DriveDistanceCommand.DriveDistanceCommandData
    Holds onto special data like DriveDistanceCommand.DriveDistanceCommandData.startingPoint and parses DriveDistanceCommand.DriveDistanceCommandData.requestedSpeed and DriveDistanceCommand.DriveDistanceCommandData.requestedTravel from the message
    HelpCommand
    Simple command to list all the commands, their arguments, and where they run
    HelpCommand.HelpCommandResponse
    Manufactures embed and does all of the heavy lifting from here
    OpenURLCommand
    Opens a URL on the server.
    OpenURLCommand.VibingCommandResponse
    Holds a url and then opens it when being processed
    PingCommand
    Gets the ping between Discord and Server
    PingCommand.PingCommandResponse
    Only needed for PingCommand.PingCommandResponse.doYourWorst(JDA)
    PlaySongCommand
    Uses Robot.chirp to play the song of the user's choosing
    QueueCommand
    Gets the music queue as managed by PlaySongCommand with pretty formatting courtesy of Chirp.getQueueAsString()
    RandomQuoteCommand
    Returns a random quote and replies with standard callback
    RoboPingCommand
    Gets the round trip ping from server to client, back to server, to discord and back to server
    RoboPingCommand.RoboCommandData
    Takes the timestamp when the message is received on the Server
    RoboPingCommand.RoboCommandResponse
    Holds onto original timestamp and uses it in RoboPingCommand.RoboCommandResponse.doYourWorst(JDA)
    ShootCommand
    Shoots a single ball with no regard to safety because screw that.
    ShutdownServerCommand
    Kills the server, leaves the robot unaffected
    ShutdownServerCommand.ShutdownServerCommandResponse
    Extra callback needed so AbstractCommand.GenericCommandResponse will not suffice.
    SkipSongCommand
    Skips the currently playing remote requested song.
    StatusCommand
    Returns a pretty listing of all activates subsystems and if they are working nominally
    StatusCommand.StatusCommandResponse
    Response requires an embed and this embed is held in pieces at StatusCommand.StatusCommandResponse.TITLE, StatusCommand.StatusCommandResponse.AUTHOR, and StatusCommand.StatusCommandResponse.REPLY_CONTENT
    TurnCommand
    This very nice command will make the robot drive! Similar to a point-to-point auton, this command does not steer, it just drives in a straight line and it is up to the user to command turns and remain clear of obstacles
    TurnCommand.TurnCommandData
    Holds onto special data like TurnCommand.TurnCommandData.startingPoint and parses TurnCommand.TurnCommandData.requestedSpeed and TurnCommand.TurnCommandData.requestedTurn from the message
    Wait5TicksThenReplyCommand
    Simple clientside multitick command to test connection and persistance.
    Wait5TicksThenReplyCommand.Wait5TicksThenReplyData
    Need to store Wait5TicksThenReplyCommand.Wait5TicksThenReplyData.ticksWaited clientside, but the server doesnt care so we dont send it
